  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DEC COVID: Immediate humanitarian assistance to most affected and vulnerable children, adolescent boys and girls and their caregivers in Ukhiya Upazila</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will remain consistent with Plan International&#x2019;s global mission to emphasize the needs of women and girls. This project will primarily focus on the host community needs and will be complementary to the existing projects in the camp. 

&#x2022;	To address child protection concerns, especially for girls and adolescent women Community Based Child Protection (CBCP) committee members, with the support of community volunteers and mentors, will conduct orientation for child and youth safe space management, training on protective and gender-responsive psychosocial support Child protection, Psychological First Aid (PFA), gender equality, SGBV, SRHR for volunteers, PSHEA and Safeguarding and refresher training on safeguarding to 1200 adolescent boys and girls. 
&#x2022;	Provide age appropriate and gender responsive support for the 1200 children and adolescents (5-9 year, 10-13 year and 14-17 year). 
&#x2022;	To reduce the further risk of infection and better prepare the community to be able to move around more safely this project will distribute reusable safety face masks to 55,000 beneficiaries in Camp 1E and in two host communities unions Raja Palong and Palong Khali. 
&#x2022;	Distribute 600 hygiene kits to 200 adolescent girls and boys in Raja Palong and 400 girls and boys in Palong Khali in Ukhiya sub-district. 
&#x2022;	Provide 448 host community households with unconditional cash transfers (Minimum Emergency Basket grant) for two months. 
&#x2022;	COVID-19 awareness messaging including adhesive stickers and poster</narrative>
  </description>
